<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-10T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-10T05:00:00-05:00" n="151" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">792.94/108: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Thailand</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grant</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-10T17:00:00+07:00">May 10,
                                    1941—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received May 10—10:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>267. The British Minister informed me this morning very confidentially
                            that he has received most reliable information to the effect that the
                            Japanese Minister at Bangkok has reported to his Government that
                            preparations are being made for a <hi rend="italic">coup d’etat</hi> in
                            Thailand with a view to organizing a new pro-Japanese Government. The
                            British Minister said he had reported the matter to the Deputy Minister
                            of Foreign Affairs for transmission to the Prime Minister.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grant</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>